msgctxt "Talk_000"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.se_co>Smoke signal<3.re_co>?<4.pa> Oh, you mean this "
"smoke?<5.pa><6.ra><7.so>This is NOT a smoke signal! As you can\n"
"plainly see, I'm in the middle of cooking!<8.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_001"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm burning it?! So then...you're saying\n"
"I've messed it up. I see."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_002"
msgid ""
"<1.so>*sigh* For some reason, no matter how\n"
"hard I try to cook something wonderful,\n"
"it always turns out badly.\n"
"I thought up this ultimate recipe myself,\n"
"too. Why is this happening?!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_003"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, I would love to! I don't mind at all.\n"
"I'm sure you'll be able to cook something\n"
"really tasty. I mean...probably.\n"
"I have recipes for a lavish meat dish,\n"
"an ancient meat dish, and an ultimate\n"
"survival dish. Which will you learn?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: single_choice
msgctxt "Talk_004"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sure thing! I'll happily teach you the\n"
"recipe for my lavish meat dish.\n"
"\n"
"First, prepare the meat you want to use.\n"
"I recommend either bird meat or steak.\n"
"Then you toss in some niiiice freeesh...\n"
"<2.te_si><3.so>ORE!!<4.te_si><5.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_005"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey! That's not nice! <2.pa>Cooking delicious\n"
"meat with shiny ore is the only way!\n"
"\n"
"How else would one create a truly lavish\n"
"meat dish, silly?!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: single_choice
msgctxt "Talk_006"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sure thing! I'll happily teach you the\n"
"recipe for my ancient meat dish.\n"
"\n"
"First, prepare the meat you want to use.\n"
"I recommend either bird meat or steak.\n"
"\n"
"And then you'll cook it with something\n"
"from a broken Guardian...\n"
"<2.te_si>\n"
"<3.so>AN ANCIENT PART!!<4.te_si><5.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_007"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey! That's not nice! <2.pa>Cooking delicious\n"
"meat with something that smacks of\n"
"history is the only way!\n"
"How else would one create an ancient\n"
"meat dish the likes of which no one\n"
"has ever seen before?!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: sound
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: single_choice
msgctxt "Talk_008"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sure thing! I'll happily teach you the\n"
"recipe for my ultimate survival dish.\n"
"\n"
"First, you'll have to defeat a monster!!<2.pa>\n"
"After that, just find yourself a cooking\n"
"pot and toss in...\n"
"<3.te_si><4.so>tons of monster parts!!<5.te_si><6.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "Talk_009"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.so>In order to survive out in the\n"
"wild, you've got to be willing\n"
"to eat anything!\n"
"That's the idea behind my\n"
"ultimate survival dish!!<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: single_choice
msgctxt "Talk_010"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Me? My name is <2.se_co>Moza<3.re_co>.<4.pa> I'm trying to\n"
"perfect my ultimate dish, so I'm training\n"
"in isolation right now.<5.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: single_choice
msgctxt "Talk_011"
msgid "<1.so>Huh?<2.pa> Who are you?!<3.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_050"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, thank you! Now I'm going to keep up\n"
"my cooking practice!\n"
"\n"
"Next up...<2.pa>adding a subtle splash\n"
"of seasoning!!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_051"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, that's too bad. It was a pretty\n"
"special recipe, too..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_052"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, it's you! You don't have to say a\n"
"word. You're back to hear the recipes\n"
"I came up with again, aren't you?\n"
"I have recipes for a lavish meat dish,\n"
"an ancient meat dish, and an ultimate\n"
"survival dish. Which will you learn?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_053"
msgid "<1.so>Do you want to hear another recipe?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_054"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My endeavors today have only added to\n"
"the wreckage that is my culinary career...\n"
"\n"
"But tomorrow... Tomorrow is definitely\n"
"the day I turn it all around!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: sound
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "Talk_055"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm?<2.pa> Oh, it's you...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You have a satisfied look on your face,\n"
"like you've accomplished something\n"
"and are all proud of it and stuff.\n"
"<3.so>Wish I knew what it was like to have\n"
"that look...\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>Well, anyway. To show off the fruits of my\n"
"training, I'm going to tell you all about\n"
"the recipes I've created!\n"
"I have recipes for a lavish meat dish,\n"
"an ancient meat dish, and an ultimate\n"
"survival dish. Which will you learn?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_056"
msgid ""
"<1.so>*sigh* Why do I mess it up every time\n"
"I try to cook?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_100"
msgid ""
"<1.so>To be honest, what I always end up\n"
"making is <2.se_co>dubious food<3.re_co>...<4.pa> Though I\n"
"don't see what's so dubious about it!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_101"
msgid ""
"<1.so>To be honest, what I always end up\n"
"making is <2.se_co>rock-hard food<3.re_co>...<4.pa> How did\n"
"it even get that rocky anyway?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
msgctxt "Talk_102"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I may end up with nothing to eat but\n"
"<2.se_co>dubious food<3.re_co>...but I won't achieve my\n"
"goal unless I make some sacrifices!\n"
"<4.so>I don't see what's so dubious about\n"
"using monster parts, though..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_103"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Even when I use ingredients I'm certain\n"
"will be perfect, there are lots of times I\n"
"still mess it up.<2.pa> Cooking is complicated."
msgstr ""

